```csharp
public static ReadOnlySpan<char> GetField(ReadOnlySpan<char> input, int n, char delimiter)
{
    int start = 0, end = 0;
    int currentField = 0;

    while (end < input.Length)
    {
        if (input[end] == delimiter)
        {
            if (currentField == n)
                return input.Slice(start, end - start);
            start = end + 1;
            currentField++;
        }
        end++;
    }

    // Handle the last field case
    if (currentField == n)
        return input.Slice(start, end - start);

    return ReadOnlySpan<char>.Empty; // Field does not exist
}
```

### Usage Example:
```csharp
ReadOnlySpan<char> input = "123 abc def".AsSpan();
int n = 1; // Second field
char delimiter = ' ';
ReadOnlySpan<char> field = GetField(input, n, delimiter);
Console.WriteLine(field.ToString()); // Output: abc
```

This function efficiently finds the n-th field using `ReadOnlySpan<char>`, providing better performance due to reduced allocations.

